-- TABLE-Albanian August CPI rises 2 pct year on year 
-- 
-- Tue Sep 09, 2014 09:34AM EDT
-- None



TIRANA, Sept 9 (Reuters) - Albania's prices rose 2 percent in August over the same month last year, boosted by prices for goods and services, including alcoholic beverages and tobacco, the Institute of Statistics said on Tuesday.

After dropping below zero for four months in a row, prices rose 0.1 percent in August over July, the Institute added.Albanian PricesAugust 2014July 2014 August 2013   Month-on-month0.1   -0.6   -0.1Year-on-year 2.0   1.81.2   Note: The Central Bank, the Bank of Albania, targets an inflation rate of around 3 percent, or in the 2 to 4 percent band.